#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:9
msgid ""
"Anura is an intuitive text extraction tool (OCR) designed for the GNOME "
"desktop. It allows you to quickly grab text from any source on your screen, "
"including videos, PDFs, images, or protected web pages."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:14
msgid "Key features include:"
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:16
msgid "High-accuracy OCR powered by Tesseract."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:17
msgid "Built-in QR code decoding and link following."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:18
msgid "Support for multiple languages with on-demand model download."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:19
msgid "Privacy-focused: no telemetry and no anonymous data collection."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:20
msgid ""
"Modern GTK4 / Libadwaita interface following GNOME Human Interface "
"Guidelines."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:22
msgid ""
"Network access is used exclusively for two purposes: downloading Tesseract "
"OCR language models on demand (sourced from GitHub), and the optional text-"
"to-speech feature powered by Google TTS. No user data or extracted text is "
"ever transmitted externally."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:28
msgid ""
"Screenshot capture uses the XDG Desktop Portal interface, which requires a "
"portal backend to be installed on the host. GNOME and KDE typically ship one "
"by default (xdg-desktop-portal-gnome / xdg-desktop-portal-kde). On other "
"desktops you may need to install a backend explicitly: xdg-desktop-portal-"
"gtk on LXQt / Xfce / MATE, xdg-desktop-portal-wlr on wlroots-based "
"compositors. Without a backend the system cannot grant Anura access to the "
"screen and the \"Take a screenshot\" action will fail."
msgstr ""

#: data/io.github.d3msudo.anura.metainfo.xml.in:38
msgid ""
"When the portal backend is unavailable or fails, Anura automatically falls "
"back to host-side screenshot tools via flatpak-spawn. To enable this "
"fallback, install at least one screenshot tool on the host system: gnome-"
"screenshot (recommended), xfce4-screenshooter, spectacle, scrot, maim, or "
"ImageMagick import. Anura tries them in order and uses the first available "
"tool."
msgstr ""

